1.	Style a simple paragraph.
●	Set the font family to Arial.
●	Change the text color to blue.
●	Set the font size to 16px.
●	Add a line height of 1.5.
●	Apply a background color of lightgray
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <title>Styled Paragraph</title>
</head>
<body>
  <p>This is a simple paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>
p {
  font-family: Arial;
  color: blue;
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.5;
  background-color: lightgray;
}
2.	Style a box using padding, margin, and border.
●	Set the width to 300px.
●	Add a padding of 20px.
●	Apply a border of 2px solid black.
●	Add a margin of 10px.
●	Set a background color to lightblue.
<div class="styled-box">
  This is a styled box.
</div>
.styled-box {
  width: 300px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 2px solid black;
  margin: 10px;
  background-color: lightblue;
}
3.	Apply hover effects to a button.
●	Set the initial background color to green.
●	Change the background color to darkgreen on hover.
●	Set the initial text color to white.
●	Change the text color to yellow on hover.
●	Add a transition effect of 0.3s for the background color.
<button class="styled-button">Hover Me</button>
.styled-button {
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.3s;
}

.styled-button:hover {
  background-color: darkgreen;
  color: yellow;
}
4)Apply a custom font and shadow to a header.
●	Import a custom font using @font-face or Google Fonts.
●	Apply the custom font to a header.
●	Set the font size to 24px.
●	Add a text shadow of 1px 1px 2px black.
●	Change the header’s color to purple.
h1 {
  font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; /* Applying the custom font */
  font-size: 24px; /* Setting the font size to 24px */
  color: purple; /* Changing the header's color to purple */
  text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px black; /* Adding a text shadow */
}
<h1>This is a header with custom font and shadow</h1>
5.	Create a button with animation.
●	Set the initial background color of the button to orange.
●	Change the background color to darkorange on hover.
●	Add a transition of 0.4s for the background color.
●	Set the font size to 18px.
●	Add padding of 10px 20px to the button.
<button class="animated-button">Click Me</button>
.animated-button {
  background-color: orange;
  color: white;
  font-size: 18px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.4s; /* Adding transition for background color */
}

.animated-button:hover {
  background-color: darkorange;
}

